11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 160 of Title 47, unless there is
13 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Motor
15 Carrier Public Safety Enforcement Act”.
16 B. The purpose of this act is to enhance public safety with
17 respect to the motor carrier industry, to foster a more consistent
18 and cohesive approach to enforcement of Oklahoma’s laws regulating
19 the motor carrier industry, and to advance the efficiency and
20 efficacy of motor carrier enforcement.
21 C. Beginning July 1, 2026, and effective June 30, 2027, all
22 powers, duties, and responsibilities for roadside investigation and
23 enforcement as well as investigation and enforcement at fixed
24 facilities, as defined by Section 1201 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
Req. No. 10049 Page 4

1 Stat utes, of the following provisions, which shall be collectively
2 referenced within this section as the “Motor Carrier Laws”, shall be
3 transferred from the Oklahoma Corporation Commission to the
4 Department of Public Safety:
5 1. Sections 161A through 180m of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
6 Statutes;
7 2. Sections 230.21 through 230.34b of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
8 Statutes;
9 3. The Trucking One-Stop Shop Act, including Sections 1166
10 through 1169 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
11 4. The Oklahoma Weigh Station Act of 2012, Sections 1200
12 through 1203 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
13 5. The Oklahoma Motor Fuel/Diesel Fuel Importer for Use Tax
14 Code, Sections 601 through 616 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
15 and
16 6. The Oklahoma Special Fuel Use Tax, Sections 701 through 723
17 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
